<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hick; Kevin Johnson, ; Craig Stanke 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 GLITZ OR VALUE? The 1994 Zagat survey of the best Southern California 
restaurants was released this week.Tops in Orange County: For food, Pascal's in 
Newport Beach. For decor: The Towers at the Surf and Sand Hotel in Laguna Beach 
and the Ritz-Carlton hotel's dining room in Dana Point. For top value: Ruby's 
on the Balboa Pier. . . . Zagat says of Ruby's: "A sentimental ode to the '50s 
burger joint." Actually, says Ruby's manager Chris Rimer, "it's from the '40s. 
That's Glenn Miller in the background. But we'll take it. This is quite a plug 
for us." 
</P>
