<HEADLINE>
<P>
'TIME FOR YOUNGER PEOPLE,' RETIRING LAWMAKER SAYS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After 17 years in Congress, Rep. Doug Applegate (D-Ohio) said Monday that he 
is ready to retire and he recommended that other old-timers do the same. 
Applegate, 65, issued a press release from his Steubenville, Ohio, office 
saying: "It is time for younger people to take the reins of government and lead 
us into the next century." 
</P>
