of 47 inmates who were in the cell next to a 10th-floor courtroom, said Los 
Angeles County Sheriff's Deputy Irma Becerra. 
</P>
<P>
 Becerra said the fight fell along racial lines with Latino and black inmates 
battling each other, though the cause was not known. Deputies broke up the 
brawl without the use of force, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Numerous recent fights in jail facilities around the county have also been 
described as being racially motivated. The three inmates injured Monday were 
sent for treatment for cuts and abrasions at the jail ward at Los Angeles 
County-USC Medical Center, Becerra said. 
