<P>
8 INJURED BY YULE TREE FIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Christmas tree fire started by a boy playing with a lighter swept through a 
Mid-City apartment Monday, injuring three adults and five children, authorities 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire was reported at 8:11 a.m. and was extinguished by residents and 
neighbors before firefighters arrived, city Fire Department spokesman Jim Wells 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Andre Dixon, 29, and a 4-month-old girl were listed in stable condition at 
California Medical Center, where they were being treated for burns and smoke 
inhalation, hospital spokeswoman Catherine Montagna said. 
</P>
<P>
 The others -- including children ages 1, 2, 5 and 8 -- were treated at 
hospitals for smoke inhalation and minor burns, then released. 
