<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: SUMMER-LIKE TEMPERATURES WARM COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TINA DAUNT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Temperatures in Ventura County soared into the high 70s and low 80s as a 
summer-like weather system moved through Southern California on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Piru was the hottest spot in the county, with a high temperature of 84 degrees 
-- about 20 degrees warmer than usual, meteorologists for the National Weather 
Service in Oxnard said. 
</P>
<P>
 The temperature reached 80 degrees in Thousand Oaks, while Ventura was a balmy 
76. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is really more like July," said meteorologist David Gomberg. "January 
should be more like mid-60s." 
</P>
<P>
 But don't get out the beach umbrella yet. Temperatures are expected to drop 
today, Gomberg said. 
</P>
<P>
 "It will be at least 10 degrees cooler," Gomberg said. TINA DAUNT 
</P>
</TEXT>
