ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: LA PALMA; COUNCIL TO CONSIDER LIMITING GARAGE SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council will discuss an ordinance today that would limit residents to 
two garage sales a year. 
</P>
<P>
 The proposed ordinance grew out of complaints that some residents were holding 
garage sales nearly every week, causing traffic snarls and littering 
neighborhoods with advertising signs. 
</P>
<P>
 The council is not expected to take a final vote tonight but probably will 
schedule a public hearing on the matter Jan. 18, city officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 If the proposed ordinance is passed, residents will have to register with the 
city before holding a garage sale. Also, residents will be prohibited from 
posting garage-sale signs on public property. 
</P>
