ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; SMART-STREET FORUMS WILL BE RESCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two public forums scheduled this week in La Habra and Anaheim to address the 
Imperial Highway Smart Street project have been postponed. Forum hosts, the 
Orange County Transportation Authority, will reschedule the public meetings, 
but have not yet decided on new dates and times. 
</P>
<P>
 The forums are to focus on the Imperial Highway Smart Street enhancements that 
include traffic signal coordination, roadway widening, raised medians and bus 
turnouts. 
</P>
<P>
 Each forum will provide information and exhibits detailing the project. 
Representatives from OCTA and local cities will be on hand to answer questions. 
 
