<HEADLINE>
<P>
ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ryan Fial 
</P>
<P>
 Edison, Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Soccer / Fullback 
</P>
<P>
 Last summer, Edison Coach Mike DiGiovanni was worried about replacing the 
stopper from the team that finished in fifth place in the Sunset League.Fial 
stepped in during summer league play and is one of the main reasons the 
Chargers are undefeated this season. Last week, he was named MVP of the Orange 
Holiday tournament after Edison beat La Habra, 1-0, in the title game. Edison 
(10-0-1) shut out three of its four opponents in the tournament. "(Fial) 
basically won the tournament for us," DiGiovanni said. 
