<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOYOLA LOSES IN OVERTIME, 92-91 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ROB FERNAS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Loyola Marymount's inability to rebound in key situations has hurt the Lions 
on numerous occasions in the past two seasons, but never more than Monday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 Fairfield forward Shannon Bowman grabbed an offensive rebound and made a short 
jump shot with three seconds left in overtime to give the Stags a 92-91 victory 
at Gersten Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
 It was perhaps the most bitter defeat in Loyola's 19-game losing streak. The 
Lions (0-9) blew an 83-78 lead in the final 33 seconds of regulation, then 
failed to box out on the defensive end after Bill Mazurie had given the Lions a 
91-90 lead on two free throws with 16 seconds left in overtime. 
</P>
<P>
 After Fairfield (3-4) brought the ball up court, guard Craig Martin drove the 
baseline and put up a driving shot that hit the front of the rim, bounced over 
the basket and into the hands of Bowman, who put the ball back in. 
</P>
<P>
 Wyking Jones led Loyola with 19 points. Mazurie, who scored all seven of the 
Lions' points in overtime, scored 12, as did freshman forward Mike O'Quinn. 
</P>
<P>
 Fairfield's Martin led all scorers with 26 points, including five three-point 
shots. ROB FERNAS 
</P>
