<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Toys R Us Announces Management Changes: Toys R Us said that Vice Chairman 
Michael Goldstein will become its chief executive and Robert C. Nakasone will 
become president and chief operating officer effective Feb. 1.The two men 
succeed Charles Lazarus, who will retain his position as chairman and head of 
the company's executive committee. Lazarus founded the giant toy retailer with 
one store in 1957. The move will allow the 70-year-old Lazarus more time to 
work on merchandising, make visits to individual stores and oversee the chain's 
expansion abroad, Goldstein said. 
</P>
