<TEXT>
<P>
 HURRAY FOR: Hollywood in Hong Kong? 
</P>
<P>
 Three years before this British dependency is to revert to Chinese rule, it is 
about to get a large dose of U.S.-style movie mania with the opening sometime 
this year of a Planet Hollywood restaurant.The chain, owned by movie stars 
Arnold Schwarzenegger, Sylvester Stallone and Bruce Willis, features a film 
memorabilia motif and already includes seven other restaurants in the United 
States, Britain and Mexico.  
</P>
<P>
 The Hong Kong outlet is just one part of a massive strategic plan aimed at 
turning Canton Road, located within a 3 1/2-square-mile shopping area at the 
tip of the colony's Kowloon Peninsula, into something like New York's West 57th 
Street. 
</P>
<P>
 Hotel Properties Ltd., the Singapore-based firm which holds the franchise for 
Planet Hollywood, also plans to open a Hard Rock Cafe on Canton Road sometime 
next year. CHRISTINE COURTNEY 
</P>
